Not fewer than 13 lives were lost in multiple automobile accidents that occurred in Bauchi within few hours intervals. Information gathered by Tribune Online revealed that the accidents occurred in Tashan Maiturare and Takandan Giwa all along the ever-busy Bauchi – Jos road in Toro LGA of the state. ALSO READ: Simple health tips to help curtail spread of coronavirus Childbirth spacing: Bauchi journalists receive training Bauchi SEC approves establishment of oil and gas academy Bauchi First lady offers free medical services to 3,000… Bauchi govt synergies to combat crimes as Gov Bala hands… The first accident which occurred at about 9 pm on Thursday involved a Peugeot J5 bus with another car in a head-on collision and burst into flame where not fewer than 10 victims died on the spot with others injured. The second accident occurred in the early hours of Friday involving a Vectra car which had a lone accident close to Takandan Giwa village when it swerved off the road into the bush leaving one dead while others were injured. The source told our correspondent that the two accidents were caused by various traffic rules infringement by the drivers of the vehicles. As at the time of filing this report, Bauchi Sector Command of the FRSC when contacted confirmed the accidents but said that it was still gathering details which it will make public as soon as possible. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! HERE IS HOW OVER 5000  NIGERIA MEN HAVE PERMANENTLY OVERCOME TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS RECENT DISCOVERY BY MEDICAL CONSULTANTS LOOK!  YOU DONT NEED TO HAVE ANY EXPERIENCE TO TRADE ONLINE,WE WILL DO IT ALL FOR YOU AND YOU WILL START EARNING A LIVING FROM TRADING ONLINE TODAY AND PROFITS WILL BE PAID TO YOUR ACCOUNT DIRECTLY. CLICK HERE TO REGISTER AND EARN CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY 